# Experiment 5 - Student Management System using Node.js, Express, MongoDB and EJS

## Name
Naomi Zephania

## UID
24BDA70345

## Objective
- Build a Student Management System with CRUD operations
- Implement backend APIs using Express.js
- Store and manage student data using MongoDB
- Render dynamic pages using EJS
- Organize the project using MVC architecture

## Technologies Used
- Software: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Mongoose, EJS, VS Code
- Tools: PNPM, Postman / Thunder Client
- Hardware: i5+ CPU, 8GB RAM (recommended)

## Features
- Add new students with name and roll number
- View a list of all students
- Update existing student information
- Delete student records
- Pagination and sorting support for student listing
- Server-side rendering using EJS templates
- RESTful API endpoints for student operations
- MVC project structure for clean and maintainable code

